---
// SlicedLabs · legal · © 2026 SlicedLabs — Privacy Policy
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
const updated = "June 22, 2026";
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy — SlicedLabs" description="How SlicedLabs collects, uses, and protects your information.">
  <section class="wrap section" style="max-width:46rem;">
    <p class="mono" data-reveal>legal</p>
    <h1 class="t-h1" data-reveal style="--i:1; margin:.3rem 0 0;"><span class="blend-text">Privacy Policy</span></h1>
    <hr class="blade" data-reveal style="--i:2; max-width:10rem; margin:1.2rem 0 1.2rem;" />
    <p class="mono" style="color:var(--muted); margin:0 0 1.4rem;">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    <div class="glass island" data-reveal style="margin-bottom:1.6rem;">
      <p style="margin:0; color:var(--muted);"><strong style="color:var(--ink);">A note.</strong> This is a good-faith starting template — not legal advice. Have a qualified attorney review it before you rely on it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" data-reveal>
      <p>SlicedLabs ("we", "us") respects your privacy. This policy explains what we collect, why, and your choices. It covers slicedlabs.io and our related pages and services.</p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>You give us:</strong> your email (newsletter, lead forms, account), and for orders your name, shipping address, and contact details.</li>
        <li><strong>Automatically:</strong> basic, privacy-respecting analytics (aggregate page views and events) to understand what's working. We do not sell your data.</li>
        <li><strong>Payments:</strong> card details are entered directly with our payment processor and are never stored on our servers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To send the newsletter and the free resources you ask for (you can unsubscribe any time).</li>
        <li>To process and fulfill orders, memberships, workshops, and digital products.</li>
        <li>To operate, secure, and improve the site, and to respond to your messages.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Service providers we use</h2>
      <p>We share the minimum necessary with trusted processors who act on our behalf: <strong>Stripe</strong> (payments), <strong>Printful</strong> (print-on-demand fulfillment), <strong>Supabase</strong> (accounts, orders, database), <strong>beehiiv</strong> (newsletter), <strong>Resend</strong> (transactional email), and <strong>Vercel</strong> (hosting and aggregate analytics). Each has its own privacy terms.</p>

      <h2>Your choices &amp; rights</h2>
      <p>You can unsubscribe from email at any time, request access to or deletion of your personal data, and close your account. To make a request, use the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. Depending on where you live, you may have additional rights under laws such as GDPR or CCPA — we honor verified requests.</p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use only essential cookies (sign-in session, your light/dark preference) and privacy-respecting analytics. We do not use third-party advertising trackers.</p>

      <h2>Data retention &amp; security</h2>
      <p>We keep personal data only as long as needed to provide the service and meet legal obligations, and we use reasonable safeguards to protect it. No method of transmission is 100% secure.</p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>The site is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect their data.</p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy; we'll revise the date above. Questions? Reach us via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
